<subSubSection id="C3234CA1FFEDFF8945B7FF5CFEC884B4" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFEDFF8945B7FF5CFDEC808B" blockId="9.[151,605,151,214]" box="[151,605,187,214]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFEDFF8945B7FF5CFF6D808B" box="[151,220,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[218,1371,189,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[200,1388,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2 A–R. Species of Macropsis, habitus, dorsal and lateral aspects. A–B, M. krishna sp. nov.; C–D, M. kundui Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; E–F, M. leucasasperae Viraktamath; G–H, M. linnavuorii Viraktamath; I–J, M. nepalica Viraktamath; K–L, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath; M–N, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; O–P, M. shrideviae Viraktamath; Q–R, M. smitae Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427924/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Figs 2</figureCitation>
A–B, 4D, 6A–I, 7A–F, H, 12A–C.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFEDFF8945B7FEE4FD9481F3" blockId="9.[151,1437,259,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Dark brown to black, shining. Margins of gena and clypellus brownish ochraceous. Eyes reddish brown, often with inner margin paler. Labium pale brown with apex dark brown. Pronotum and mesonotum black. Thoracic sternites and pleurites dark brown with paler markings. Forewing shining brownish black, anal margin, claval sutures, and some of the outer apical cell and subapical cells hyaline. Abdominal sternites brown to black with paler posterior margins. Legs dark brown to black.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFEDFF8945E7FE50FD3582AC" blockId="9.[151,1437,259,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">
Head obtusely angled medially, slightly narrower than pronotum. Crown elevated above the level of pronotum, medially much shorter than next to eyes. Face more or less flattish, obliquely depressed across bases of antennae, and on either side of clypellus; rugose punctate, including eyes broader than long. Lateral margins of clypellus well defined, broadened in distal 0.33. Pronotum about as long as or shorter than mesonotum, slightly convex, with oblique rugae converging on median line, posterior margin slightly concave. Mesonotum finely rugose punctate except shagreen basal triangles. Forewing polished, shiny with raised prominent venation, three anteapical cells, inner anteapical cell either closed or open; 2.4–2.6 × as long as wide. Tergal apodemes at base of abdomen more or less rectangular, in contact with each other medially (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFEDFF89479DFD54FCA98290" box="[701,792,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
); sternal apodemes (2S) longer than broad at base, apices narrowed distally to pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFEDFF89473DFD30FDC682AC" box="[541,631,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFEDFF8945E7FD1CFF6483B0" blockId="9.[151,1437,259,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis id="B94DC338FFEDFF8945E7FD1CFEDE834B" box="[199,367,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer dorsal margin more or less straight, posterior margin hyaline, rest dark pigmented; ventral pygofer process short, bluntly pointed apically, not reaching dorsal margin. Style reaching apex of subgenital plate, strongly curved dorsally near apex and abruptly narrowed, with series of setae subapically on dorsal margin. Aedeagus with well developed dorsal apodeme and preatrium, the former slightly longer than latter, shaft broad at base and narrowed to apex, distal half of shaft much thinner, gonopore on ventral margin surrounded by rim laterally and basally, rim unevenly crenulated; dorsal connective H-shaped, with the dorsal arms much longer than proximal arms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFEDFF8945E7FC10FF548420" blockId="9.[151,1437,259,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis id="B94DC338FFEDFF8945E7FC10FE34844F" box="[199,389,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Sternite VII narrowed posteriorly, with median inverted V-shaped excavation, broader basally than median length (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFEDFF8944A4FBFCFE51846B" box="[388,480,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Valvula I straight blade-like, dorsal sculpture strigate, reaching dorsal margin and confined to distal 0.33 length (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFEDFF8944D3FBD8FD878407" box="[499,566,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
C–D). Valvula II straight with prominent five teeth in distal 0.33 length (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFEDFF89404FFBD8FF148420" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFEDFF8945E7FB60FEC884B4" blockId="9.[151,1437,259,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis id="B94DC338FFEDFF8945E7FB60FECC84FF" bold="true" box="[199,381,1159,1185]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFEDFF8944EAFB60FDE284FC" box="[458,595,1159,1186]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="4.55" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFEDFF8947BEFB60FC9984FC" box="[670,808,1159,1186]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and also across posterolateral angles of pronotum. Female 4.7–5.0 mm long, 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFEDFF89477FFB4CFD568498" box="[607,743,1195,1222]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.6 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFEDFF8946C7FB4CFBDE8498" box="[999,1135,1195,1222]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5499999999999998" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="1.5499999999999998" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.7 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
